<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/171> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #171" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 3.1.1; Diod. 11.74.1; Dion. Hal. 9.59.1; Chr. 354 (Mamerco II et Vivulano); Fast. Hyd. (Aemilio II et Bibulano); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod.; Degrassi 91, 358f. Fabius held command against the Aequi (Liv. 3.1.8; Dion. Hal. 9.59.3-5); while Aemilius fought the Sabines and proposed the founding of the citizen colony at Antium (Liv. 3.1.2-5; Dion. Hal. 9.59.1-3)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/170> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #170" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On Aemilius' name, see 470, note 1; that of Fabius is preserved in full in Fast. Cap. for 465. On the filiation, see also Dion. Hal. 9.22.5, and 59.1." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/162> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #162" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 2.61.1; Diod. 11.69.1; Dion. Hal. 9.51.1; Chr. 354 (Potito II et Mamerco); Fast. Hyd. (Emilio et Valerio); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod.; Degrassi 91, 358f. Valerius fought the Aequi and Aemilius the Sabines (Liv. 2.62.1-4; Dion. Hal. 9.55.1-4). On Valerius, see Münzer, Gent. Val. 35, no. 3." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/161> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #161" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On the name Valerius, see 483. Diodorus has the cognomen Poplicola. Aemilius' cognomen Mamercus is preserved in Diod. and Chr. 354 on both 470 and 467. Dion. Hal. (9.51.4) calls the Consul's father Lucius but the Consul Tiberius (9.51.1, and 59.1). Livy has Titus both years, but Diod. has Titus in 470 and Tiberius in 467." .
